    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND SLEEVES - CONNECTING
        ROD, PISTON &#38; RING - CLEANING
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CLEANING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the aluminum pistons using a soap and water solution; soak and then clean piston,
                using a non-metallic brush.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Never use a caustic solution or a wire brush for cleaning the aluminum pistons.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">All piston ring grooves must be cleaned thoroughly. Be sure the two drilled or cast oil
                holes in the oil ring groove are open.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The following disassembled components may be cleaned using a suitable solvent:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Piston rings</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Piston pins</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Piston pin retainers</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Connecting rods</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Connecting rod caps</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Connecting rod bolts</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean all rod bolt holes and threads thoroughly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the oil hole at the top of the rod. Make sure it is not blocked.</para>
